@node "Document_0" "Disclaimer"

Disclaimer
~~~~~~~~~~

ACP-Page is as long freely Distributable as long as the Archive Contents stay
intact! At least these files should be in the Archive:

doors/ACP-Page2.0 ......... Main Program ...................... 11080 Bytes
doors/ACP-Page2.0.c ....... Source Code ........................ 8973 Bytes
doors/ACP-Page.ansianim ... The Animation Sequence ............  7861 Bytes
ACP-Page2.0.doc ........... This File .......................... 4604 Bytes
ACP-Page2.0.guide ......... The .guide Version ................. 5431 Bytes
libs/gtlayout.library ..... Olsen's layout library ............ 83416 Bytes

Full Archive Size: 62547 Bytes

@endnode

@node "Document_1" "Introduction"

Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~

ACP-Page2.0 is no longer limited to the Excelsior! BBS Package, because in
this Version it is a simple AmigaOS program without using any E! Commands. Due
the reason that I don't know how to install DOS-Doors in other BBS Packages
like DLG, CNet, ... please have a look at your manual. If your BBS Software
don't support DOS-Doors ACP-Page2.0 is unuseable for you. Sorry...

@endnode

@node "Document_2" "General Installation"

General Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

First Copy ACP-Page2.0 into your DOORS:, if you haven't assigned it, you
should know yourself where to find it. Copy the files in the libs/#? and
doors/#? directory of the ACP-Page2.0 archive to the matching dirs on your
Harddisk.  For further Installation have a look at your Manual. E! Sysop
continue reading at E! Installation.

@endnode

@node "Document_3" "E! Installation"

E! Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

First Copy ACP-Page2.0 and ACP-Page.ansianim into your DOORS:, if you haven't
assigned it, you should know yourself where to find it. Further copy
libs/gtlayout.library to libs, check out if you have a newer version of the
library installed before!

Then edit the EX.BBSMenus File. Primary you have to find the following line:

610,  C,  0,  "1-32", ""

Now insert the following text between the two '"'s:

\#4Doors:ACP-Page2.0 %1

Save the File, and select the Master Window's Pull-Down-Menu
Extras/Re-Load/Menus. Thats all for the Installation..

@endnode

@node "Document_4" "Check it out"


Check it out
~~~~~~~~~~~~

Now make a Sysop-Login to your BBS, and type C (or the command you chose to
launch the Door) at the main Menu. If everything is installed correctly you
should see something like that:

                              .-----------------.
                              |   ACP-Page2.0   |
                     .-----------------------------------.
                     |  >>> ENTER a REASON for CHAT <<<  |
.----------------------------------------------------------------------------.
|                                                                            |
`----------------------------------------------------------------------------'
                     |        by  ACP-Development        |
                     `-----------------------------------'
                              |  (C) 1994/95    |
                              `-----------------'

Enter a chat-reason and... a window pops up at the Workbench Screen! If you
feel to chat to the paging User click the 'OK Let's chat' gadget in the Window
and the user will be informed that you will enter chat-mode soon, otherwise
dont touch it or press 'Deny Chat' - it closes itself after a few seconds. The
user won't notice that you are at home.

@endnode

@node "Document_5" "ANSI-Animation"

ANSI-Animation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


The displayed animation can be replaced by any selfmade one. We used DIed to
generate a nice one. If you make your own, feel free to send it us, we will
consider to release it with the next update of ACP-Page.

@endnode

